          "title": "Judgment begins at the house of God",
          "body": "Verses 17-18 turn the screw. *Judgment* (*krima*) is not only a future event over the wicked; it is a present process *beginning* with God's household. Peter draws on Ezekiel 9:6, where the marking and slaying of Jerusalem begins at the sanctuary. The believers' fiery ordeal *is* God's purifying judgment-fire moving through His own people first. If this is what God's people endure, what awaits *those who do not obey the gospel of God*? Verse 18 then cites Proverbs 11:31 LXX verbatim: *if it is with difficulty that the righteous is saved, what will become of the godless man and the sinner?* The argument is *a minori ad maius* — from the lesser to the greater. Salvation is real, but it runs through fire. There is no easy passage."
